Program: Outlook
Title: 11/08/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00jb7dk
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 15 Aug 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, Mohamad "Boriz" Fawad, the Afghan interpreter who dreamed of joining the British Army tells us how he felt when he was told he wasn't eligible. Also, the Canadian man who's cycling around the world to challenge perceptions of mental illness and making some friends along the way. And the reality TV contestant who learned her business skills from her hard working Chinese parents. Show less